7. Apple Open Transport static glue (macppc distribution only)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Files:  OpenTransportAppPPC.o, OpenTptInetPPC.o
Source: Extracted from Apple's final MPW release (MPW-GM disk image),
        which Apple distributed publicly at
        ftp://ftp.apple.com/developer/Tool_Chest/Core_Mac_OS_Tools/.
        That server is long gone; tools/fetch_otglue.sh pulls the same
        image from a public mirror of the original Apple FTP tree.
Used:   Linked into the PowerPC Mac OS build (build/macppc) so that
        InitOpenTransport and OTOpenInternetServices resolve correctly on
        Open Transport 1.x. The object files are fetched at build time
        from a public Apple mirror (see tools/fetch_otglue.sh) and are
        never committed to the Relic source tree; they ship only inside
        the compiled macppc binaries distributed with Relic releases.

These object files are Copyright (c) Apple Computer, Inc. They are Apple's
Open Transport static link glue, originally shipped as part of the MPW and
Universal Interfaces & Libraries developer tools. They are included in the
compiled macppc binary under the terms of the original Apple distribution.
No additional license text accompanies the object files; consult Apple's
MPW / Universal Interfaces license for details.

